  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The previously introduced parametric choice models fully depend on the choice of their underlying parameters.",
    "These parameters are typically unknown and need to be chosen or estimated in practice.",
    "Likewise, the attributes driving the choice process need to be selected, which is a potential source of specification errors (Strauss et al. 2018).",
    "Moreover, parametric choice models assume that the choice behaviour can be captured by a given functional form.",
    "Yet, the specified functional form may not adequately capture the actual choice behaviour (see Strauss et al. 2018)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Likewise, the attributes driving the choice process need to be selected, which is a potential source of specification errors (Strauss et al. 2018).",
